offset by the significant decline in catastrophe losses. catastrophe losses included in claims and claim adjustment expenses in 2009 totaled $278million, compared with $541million in
2008. catastrophe losses in 2009 primarily resulted from several wind and hail storms, as well as flooding. catastrophe losses in 2008 primarily resulted from hurricanes ike and gustav, as well as
tornado, wind and hail storms in various regions of the united states throughout the year. net favorable prior year reserve development in 2009 totaled $135million, compared with
$143million in 2008. net favorable prior year reserve development in 2009 primarily reflected favorable loss development related to hurricanes ike and katrina, as well as the 2007 california
wildfires.
