10. earnings per share
basic earnings per share was computed by dividing income available to common shareholders by the weighted average number of common shares outstanding during the period. the computation
of diluted earnings per share reflected the effect of potentially dilutive securities.
on
january1, 2009, the company adopted the updated guidance related to earnings per share as described in note1. the impact of the adoption of this guidance was a
reduction of previously reported basic and diluted earnings per share by $0.03 per share and $0.01 per share, respectively, for the year ended december31, 2008.
